gas_tracker.common.what_does_gas_refer_t: What does gas refer to on the blockchain?
gas_tracker.common.how_can_i_check_chain: How can I check {{chainName}} gas fees?
gas_tracker.common.you_can_easily_check_: You can easily check live {{chainName}} gas fees on this page. The gas tracker shows current gas prices in {{currencyUnit}} and estimated transaction times for different priority levels (fast, normal, slow).
gas_tracker.common.what_is_the_average_g: What is the average gas fee for {{chainName}} transactions?
gas_tracker.common.the_average_gas_fee_f: The average gas fee for {{chainName}} transactions varies based on network congestion. Check the current gas prices above to see real-time rates and plan your transactions accordingly.
gas_tracker.common.how_does_blockscout_c: How does Blockscout calculate gas fees?
gas_tracker.common.blockscout_calculates: Blockscout calculates gas fees based on recent transaction data from the blockchain. We analyze the gas prices of recently mined blocks to provide accurate estimates for different transaction priority levels.
